         (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Houghton Library, Harvard University ]">MH-H</span>: Tucker Papers)
       </span>
      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA06d059n1-ptr" id="PJA06d059n1">1</a>
      
   <p>Muscoe Livingston agreed to serve as second lieutenant (Samuel Tucker to the Commissioners, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-06-02-0054" class="document">29 April</a>, below).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA06d059n2-ptr" id="PJA06d059n2">2</a>
      
   <p>For Tuckers orders, see the Commissioners letter to him of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-06-02-0017" class="document">13 April</a> (above).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA06d059n3-ptr" id="PJA06d059n3">3</a>
      
   <p>That of 12 April (not found), but see John Bondfield to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, 28 April, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-06-02-0048&amp;expandNote=PJA06d054n1#PJA06d054n1" class="document">note 1</a> (above).</p>

